AGI - "Great proximity and interest" to the case of his daughter Ilaria were expressed this morning by the President of the Republic Sergio Mattarella >in a phone call to Roberto Salis>. He learns AGI from legal sources. Sergio Mattarella called the father of Ilaria Salis> this morning to express his closeness: in the course of the interview the President of the Republic said that he hoped they were different days and that he well understood his state of mind. Mattarella also assured that it will do what it is in its possibilities, that they are not wide on the operating plane and pass obviously through the government. Salis thanked a lot for the call and speed of the reply and explained that, with his letter, he wanted to signal the disparity of treatment between two Italian citizens. The Head of State told him that this is the difference between our system, inspired by European values, and their system; and that this disparity affects our public opinion. Salis thanked him and Mattarella assured him that later you will be able to resent. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
The call of the Head of State arrives after yesterday Roberto Salis sent him an email asking for his intervention and "to move the government that did nothing". Ilaria Salis has been recruited in the prison of Budapest for 13 months with the accusation of having assaulted two militants of extreme right >. The magic judges have repeatedly rejected the request to discard her and grant her the domiciles, the last two days ago.
&nbsp;
The defence has already filed an appeal against this decision, in view of the forthcoming hearing scheduled on 24 May, and announced that it will also address the European Court of Human Rights asking for the condemnation of Hungary for the "inhuman and degrading" conditions reserved to the teacher. In the letter to President Mattarella, Salis also referred to the different treatment reserved to Gabriele Marchesi>, the young defendant in Hungary for the same crimes of Ilaria. The Court of Appeal of Milan rejected for him the request for delivery by Hungary underlining the risk of a detention that does not respect the inviolable rights of the person.
<h2> Women's father does not exclude domiciles
Roberto Salis does not exclude that the daughter can be granted domiciles in Hungary > even before the next hearing, scheduled for May 24. "We appealed and now the decision on domiciles passes to second-degree judges, perhaps there might be some opportunity even before May 24th," said RaiNews24. "I believe that action should be taken with a different piglio from the executive," added Salis, "the separation of powers in Hungary is a joke: if the Italian government will press properly there may be a rethink."
&nbsp;
The father of the woman in prison in Budapest&nbsp; he defined "a step towards the right direction" the choice of the Court of Appeal of Milan to reject the request for extradition for Marchesi. Commenting on the call received by the President of the Republic, Salis said "very happy": "I didn't expect such a quick answer. >Note that on such serious cases some institutions have the right sense of urgency, I was struck by a representative of the institutions capable of being empathic with the citizens, I highly appreciated it". The call came to the next day of the letter sent to Quirinale by Salis himself after Thursday a court in Budapest had said no to the domiciles.
