AGI - In water to raise awareness on the issues of disability and in particular autism and serious mental disorders. This is the meaning of the "collective embrace >" that will be held simultaneously in nine Italian cities on 6 and 7 April, week in which the World Day of Awareness on Autism is celebrated.
&nbsp;
A 30-hour pool marathon (from 7.30 of 6 April to 13.30 of the day after)>, promoted by the social cooperative T.m.a. Group, in which everyone can participate by swimming, floating, standing in the lane for a minimum of 15 minutes along with the boys who carry out during the year the Tma (Terapia multisistemica in acqua) - method Caputo-Ippolito.
&nbsp;
It explains a note of a therapy that uses water as an emotional, sensory, motor activator, able to push the person with communication disorders, relationship, autistic spectrum disorder to a meaningful relationship. It is an intervention that uses cognitive-behavioural strategies. Supports better management of emotions, autonomy and social interaction.
&nbsp;
All participants will communicate their name and meters in the bathing assistant. The meters in the pool will symbolically represent the attempt to approach the problems of children's families with autistic spectrum disorder. A way to share with them a small part of the path of their lives and to "ab-brace" their causes aimed at recognizing the rights of their special children, often denied".
&nbsp;
A sign of closeness and sharing through sport that manages to break down barriers and make everyone equal. The proceeds collected by donations will be donated to the families of the autistic boys to offer them the possibility to make multisystem therapy in water.
&nbsp;
"For eight years the event has welcomed more and more cities and pools that have shown themselves happy to participate in such an important cause - says Dr. Giovanni Caputo, creator of multi-system therapy in water - For us it is a source of great pride that more and more people participate in this event including the spirit. It is fundamental to put a light on our boys and their abilities that sometimes go far beyond expectations and become the reason why we cannot put limits on their growth but continue to work for them to try to improve their quality of life".
